# real_number

- real number`:=` $x: x = n + 0.d_1d_2d_3d_4\ldots$ where $n$ is an [integer](integer___20250618_1132_14.pd) and $d_i$ is a decimal digit.

This means that
$$n + \frac{d_1}{10} + \frac{d_2}{100} + \ldots \frac{d_k}{10^{k}} \le x < n + \frac{d_1}{10} + \frac{d_2}{100} + \ldots \frac{d_k}{10^{k}} + \frac{1}{10^{k}}, \forall k \in \mathbb{Z}_{1}^{+}$$

# rational powers
- $b^{\frac{p}{q}} = \sqrt[q]{b^{p}}$

# arbitary real values
- if $b > 1$, $b^{n+\frac{d_1}{10} + \ldots + \frac{d_k}{10}} \le b^{x} < b^{n + \frac{d_1}{10} \ldots + \frac{d_k}{10^{k}} + \frac{1}{10^{k}}}$. We sandwich the number between two known values.
- if $b < 1$, we define $b^{x} = \left( \frac{1}{b} \right) ^{-x}$

# examples
Constant $e$, $\pi, \phi$

